---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="Alexandra Kelstrom is a software engineer, responsible AI advocate, and the person behind codewizwit. From bartender to AI enablement leader, this is the story."
>
  <article class="about">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="about-hero section-cream section" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
      <div class="container about-hero-inner">
        <img
          src="/images/image.webp"
          alt="Alexandra Kelstrom portrait"
          class="about-portrait"
          width="560"
          height="747"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <div>
          <p class="label label-gold">Hello world, I'm Alexandra.</p>
          <h1 id="about-heading" class="about-title">
            The wiz who dove in sideways.
          </h1>
          <p class="about-lede">
            AI Enablement Engineer, responsible AI advocate, and living proof that
            the path doesn't have to be straight.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 1: The Story -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="act1-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label label-gold">Act I</p>
        <h2 id="act1-heading">The story</h2>
        <div class="act1-layout">
          <div class="prose">
            <p>
              With roots in Chicago, I lived in six different countries outside
              the US: Taiwan, Latvia, Czech Republic, England, Scotland, and Poland.
              That kind of movement taught me how to read rooms fast and adapt
              to anything.
            </p>
            <p>
              I studied Media and Design at DePaul University in Chicago, then
              bartended for ten years before getting into tech. The service
              industry taught me empathy as an operational skill: reading
              people, understanding needs, solving problems in real-time.
            </p>
            <p>
              Then COVID hit. I got furloughed. I invested my life savings in
              the UPenn LPS Coding Bootcamp and received my first Software
              Engineer job offer the day I graduated. That pivot wasn't
              reckless. It was a calculated bet on myself that paid off big time.
            </p>
            <p>
              Now I coach engineering teams and build systems that keep humans
              at the center of AI adoption. Every room I've been in has prepared
              me for this one.
            </p>
          </div>
          <figure class="about-door">
            <img
              src="/images/door.jpg"
              alt="Red door with stenciled city names: Chicago, Gdansk, Riga, Taipei and others"
              width="998"
              height="1734"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>The doors that led me here</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 2: The Work -->
    <section class="section-dark section" aria-labelledby="act2-heading">
      <div class="container act2-layout">
        <div>
          <p class="about-dark-label">Act II</p>
          <h2 id="act2-heading" class="about-dark-heading">The work</h2>
          <div class="prose about-dark-prose">
            <p>
              The engineering came first: applications, automated tests,
              component libraries. What carried through all of it was a commitment to quality
              and solving problems with real empathy for the people on the
              other side of the screen.
            </p>
            <p>
              Once ChatGPT beta was released in late 2022, everything began
              to change for me. First, I used it in a personal setting and
              then I increasingly experimented with using other AI models for
              engineering work. I figured out how to use
              AI to build with my intent and my style but 100x faster, and the
              quality held. That was the aha moment. But I felt the tension
              just as fast: if AI can do this, what happens to the people?
              That question consumed me, and the perspective I was building,
              alongside the engineering work, naturally wove me into an AI
              enablement role.
            </p>
            <p>
              Now I work with engineering teams and figure out how AI fits.
              What to automate, what to protect, where the human judgment
              still matters. I build frameworks and shape how teams think
              about responsible adoption. The frameworks came from the work
              itself. Experimenting, trying things, seeing what landed and
              what missed, and shaping that into something others could use.
            </p>
            <p>
              It's part coaching, part building, part reading the room. The
              inflection point of everything I've learned.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figure class="act2-figure">
          <img
            src="/images/ai-summit.jpeg"
            alt="Alexandra at AI Summit New York, placing a tile on an interactive pixel art wall"
            class="act2-photo"
            width="768"
            height="1024"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>AI Summit NY 2025</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Hot Dog -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="hot-dog-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="hot-dog-heading" class="hot-dog-section-title">
          And yes, <a href="/the-hot-dog" class="link">the hot dog is a whole thing.</a>
        </h2>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 3: Beyond the Code -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="act3-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label label-gold">Act III</p>
        <h2 id="act3-heading">Beyond the code</h2>
        <div class="beyond-grid">
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Soundtrack</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Huge music nerd. Soul, jazz, rock, oldies, reggae, indie. Hip-hop and doo-wop are my favorites. Always loud.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Fuel</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Good meals start the best conversations. Great snacks start the best ideas.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Fiction</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Sci-fi. Always pondering the future we're building.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Eye</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">DePaul Media &amp; Design grad. Visual thinker solving technical problems.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Superpower</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Empathy. Understanding people, anticipating needs, and turning that into strategic problem solving. The bartender instinct never left.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Roots</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">
              With roots in Chicago, I lived in six different countries outside the US.
              Dual citizen (US + Czech Republic). Philadelphia is currently where I call home.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .about-portrait {
    width: clamp(180px, 22vw, 280px);
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 15%;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about-lede {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 36rem;
  }

  .act1-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-door {
    position: sticky;
    top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about-door img {
    width: 280px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }


  .about h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .act2-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr clamp(260px, 32vw, 380px);
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .act2-photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }

  .about figcaption {
    margin-top: var(--space-3xs);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .section-dark figcaption {
    color: var(--color-gray-light);
  }

  .about-dark-label {
    color: var(--color-gray-light);
  }

  .about-dark-heading {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .about-dark-prose {
    color: var(--color-gray-light);
  }

  .hot-dog-section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
  }

  .about .prose a {
    color: var(--color-gold-dark);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .about .prose a:hover {
    color: var(--color-gold-hover);
  }

  .section-dark .prose a {
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .section-dark .prose a:hover {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .beyond-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  .beyond-item {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-gray-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .beyond-label {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xs);
  }

  .beyond-text {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .about-inline-link {
    color: var(--color-gold-dark);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .about-inline-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-gold-hover);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-hero-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .about-portrait {
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .about-lede {
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .act1-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-door {
      text-align: center;
      position: static;
    }

    .about-door img {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 360px;
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .act2-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .act2-figure {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .act2-photo {
      max-width: 280px;
      margin-inline: auto;
      position: static;
    }

    .beyond-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .beyond-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
